rComments: The lectures were interesting. However, the TAs were unreasonably hard markers, it was as if they wanted the students to do poorly. The final movie analysis was fun to do but there were no instructions provided as to how to structure the analysis. The midterm/exam essay questions were provided but the expectations of the answers were sky high.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Get ready to read', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: Lectures were always structured well, and they followed a logical order. Holly was a really kind & caring professor. The final movie analysis was tough as we weren't given clear instructions as to how to write/structure the paper. Didn't focus much on sexuality &  learned sort of obvious things about gender. I wish race would've been discussed more

This class was my favourite class. The lectures were so interesting, organized and easy to follow. The readings were always interesting as well. She was very clear on what she was looking for in terms of assignments and exams. It is obvious she genuinely cares about her students, and people in general. I would recommend this class to everyone.

Super helpful and such a great prof.  All of her lectures were really interesting and gave you knew ways to look at things.  Also, when I couldn't make it to her office hours, she offered to call me to answer my questions about the assignment, which no prof has ever offered to do.  I wish I could take this course again, it was great.
